 "coaching": {
  "headline": "A 43-minute loss into two healers with zero anti-heal — the exact long game your build sheet keeps warning you about. You lost the map (6 towers to 11) and the Fangtooth, and no amount of a blind-pick Legion popping off saved it.",
  "team": "Mourn + Bayle on the enemy = two healers, anti-heal flagged mandatory, and once again nobody bought it. In a 20-minute game you can snowball past that; in a 43-minute grind you cannot — they out-healed your trades, took 11 towers to your 6, and snowballed the Fangtooth (11:00, theirs). Your favored lanes (Willy's Shinbi offlane, Xeebs' Khaimera jungle) won on paper but the carry/mid/support side was all unfavored, and Goldilocks blind-picking Legion (zero recorded games) into a losing draft is exactly the gamble that doesn't pay in a long game. The pattern is now eight games deep: you never buy anti-heal, and it costs you specifically in the games that go long.",
  "whatShiftedIt": "One anti-heal item across the team turns a 43-minute heal-fest into a closeable game — this is the single highest-leverage habit you're missing. Second: stop blind-picking into a losing draft (Legion, 0 games) and respect that your carry/mid/support lanes were all behind.",
  "perPlayer": {
   "7c8ab99c-31c5-4ea5-a6fa-e0d6417c3f1b": "Adele support, 1/10/12, and it was your FIRST game on the hero — ten deaths on a blind-pick enchanter into a losing lane is how the backline gets run over. You're a support main; pick from your pool, and you're the player who should be screaming for anti-heal vs Mourn+Bayle.",
   "16f28434-561f-4f23-9454-40321f4a1ef3": "Legion carry, 13/5/5 on ZERO recorded games — a blind pick that statline-carried but couldn't close because the team had no anti-heal vs two healers. Great mechanical game; reckless draft. Don't first-time a hero in a 5-stack ranked game into a bad matchup.",
   "a0c393cc-1437-4bdc-8168-64676ce2166c": "Zinx mid, 3/6/14, into a losing Gideon lane and double-flagged (no anti-heal, no armor vs 3 physical). Your enabling was there (14 assists) but six deaths in a lane you were behind in compounded the deficit. Anti-heal on you specifically matters into the double-healer comp.",
   "10edbf65-457d-48d0-9151-9df5b4fcb40a": "Shinbi offlane, 3/7/7 — your lane was FAVORED (sim: yours all game) and you went 3/7. As shot-caller, a favored lane you lose on the scoreboard is the one to own; you also skipped armor into a 3-physical comp. Win your winning lanes and call the anti-heal.",
   "a412baf3-dd17-4f89-8ecf-9d0704f3a79e": "Khaimera jungle, 7/11/6, 65% comfort — eleven deaths is the number. You're the best-on-role player here but you fed the snowball; in a losing-objective game the jungler dying 11 times hands them the map. Tighter pathing, fewer forced fights when behind."
  }
